Name: Abraham Lincoln Birthplace National Historical Park
Acadia National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Vehicle reservations are not required for any other areas of the park, or for visitors who enter the area by foot, bike, or taxi. Vehicle reservations provide a timed entry, but do not require a departure time until 10 pm, when the road closes to vehicles. Reservations do not permit re-entry. Reservations are per vehicle, not per person. Reservations do not assign a specific parking space. Parking is prohibited outside of designated spaces. Cadillac is not served by the Island Explorer bus system.

Name: Adams National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Access into the historic homes is by a ticketed, timed tour.  Every individual in your party must have a ticket.  It is strongly recommended that tickets be purchased in advance on Adams National Historical Park's Recreation.gov page.

Name: Aleutian Islands World War II National Historic Area
Allegheny Portage Railroad National Historic Site
Appomattox Court House National Historical Park
Arches National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: From April 1 through October 31, 2023, visitors entering the park in a vehicle between 7 am and 4 pm will need to have already purchased a Timed Entry Ticket from Recreation.gov before reaching the park. One ticket is needed per vehicle. This fee is a Recreation.gov service charge, so it is not waived by any of the interagency passes.

Name: Arlington House, The Robert E. Lee Memorial
Badlands National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Fee covers the entry of a private vehicle and its occupants for 7 days

Name: Bandelier National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Pass covers all persons traveling in a single, private, non-commercial vehicle (car, truck, camper, or van up to 15 passengers). Auto passes are non-transferable and not replaced if lost or stolen.  Entrance passes do not cover camping fees.

Name: Bent's Old Fort National Historic Site
Big Bend National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15 passenger capacity or less); valid for 7 days.

Name: Big South Fork National River & Recreation Area
Black Canyon Of The Gunnison National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: 7-Day Vehicle Pass.  Entrance fees cover all persons in a single, private, non-commercial vehicle.

Name: Blackstone River Valley National Historical Park
Boston African American National Historic Site
Boston Harbor Islands National Recreation Area
Brices Cross Roads National Battlefield Site
Brown v. Board of Education National Historical Park
Bryce Canyon National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15 passenger capacity or less) and all occupants.

Name: Cabrillo National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all its passengers.

Name: Cane River Creole National Historical Park
Canyonlands National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15 passenger capacity or less) and all its occupants.

Name: Cape Cod National Seashore
Entrance Fee Desc: Pass is for one private, non-commercial vehicle — passenger cars, pickup trucks, RVs and vans.

Name: Cape Henry Memorial Part of Colonial National Historical Park
Designation: Part of Colonial National Historical Park

Name: Capitol Reef National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: An entrance fee is charged per vehicle for the Scenic Drive.

Name: Captain John Smith Chesapeake National Historic Trail
Capulin Volcano National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits private, non-commercial vehicle (15 passenger capacity or less) and all occupants to Capulin Volcano National Monument. The maximum size of a vehicle allowed on the Volcano Road is 26 feet in length and/or 8 feet in width. Passes may be upgraded to annual passes within 7 days of purchase.

Name: Carl Sandburg Home National Historic Site
Carlsbad Caverns National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: A entrance time reservation must be purchased to enter Carlsbad Cavern. Time entry ensures a more enjoyable experience and helps to protect the cave formations.

Name: Carter G. Woodson Home National Historic Site
Castillo de San Marcos National Monument
Cedar Breaks National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee is for visitors, age 16 or older and is valid for 7 days from the time of purchase.

Name: Cedar Creek & Belle Grove National Historical Park
Chaco Culture National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee allows all persons traveling in one private, non-commercial vehicle (car/truck/van) to enter the park to visit for up to 7 days from the date of purchase.

Name: Charles Young Buffalo Soldiers National Monument
Chesapeake & Ohio Canal National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Pass is for one private, non-commercial vehicle — passenger cars, pickup trucks, RVs and vans — and is valid at the Great Falls area of the Chesapeake and Ohio Canal National Historical Park on the Maryland side of the Potomac River and Great Falls Park on the Virginia side of the Potomac River.

Name: Chickamauga & Chattanooga National Military Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance fees only apply to Point Park, on Lookout Mountain. If you plan to visit Chickamauga Battlefield, parts of Lookout Mountain Battlefield, exclusive of Point Park, Missionary Ridge, Orchard Knob, Signal Point, or Moccasin Bend National Archeological District, entrance to the park areas is FREE.

Name: Colonial National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Adult (16 and older) -$15; good for 7 days entrance to Yorktown Battlefield (and NPS areas at Historic Jamestowne); can be upgraded to see Preservation Virginia areas at Historic Jamestowne for an additional $15 at the Historic Jamestowne Visitor Center. Yorktown Battlefield will not be selling the $30 entrance permit for Historic Jamestowne.

Name: Colorado National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: $25 for a private vehicle, this pass is good for 7 days.

Name: Crater Lake National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This is the summer entrance fee and is charged from mid-May through the end of October.  Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15-passenger capacity or less) and all occupants. Good for 7 days.

Name: Craters Of The Moon National Monument & Preserve
Entrance Fee Desc: This per-vehicle fee applies to private, non-commercial vehicles and provides entrance into the park for seven consecutive days. The fee covers the driver and any passengers.

Name: Cumberland Island National Seashore
Entrance Fee Desc: Cumberland Island National Seashore has a per-person entrance fee. This fee is waived for America the Beautiful pass holder plus three adults. Must present pass at time of check-in.

Name: Dayton Aviation Heritage National Historical Park
Death Valley National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This permit allows all persons traveling with the permit holder in one single private, non-commercial vehicle (car/truck/van) to leave and re-enter the park as many times as they wish during the 7-day period from the date of purchase.

Name: Delaware Water Gap National Recreation Area
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance fee for beaches and boat launches. Fee is good for one vehicle and it's passengers (up to 7 people).

Name: Denali National Park & Preserve
Entrance Fee Desc: Denali charges an entrance fee year-round. Youth age 15 or younger are free. For people age 16 or older, the $15 entrance fee provides a 7-day entrance permit. Be prepared to show your receipt or pass (digital or physical) if requested by park staff.

Name: Devils Tower National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Fee for a single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all its passengers.  Note: In summer it's a good idea to arrive at the entrance station before 10 am or after 4 pm to avoid congestion and find better parking options.

Name: Dinosaur National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15 passenger capacity or less) and all its occupants. Admission is good for seven consecutive days. You can come and go any time with your seven-day pass.

Name: Edgar Allan Poe National Historic Site
El Camino Real de Tierra Adentro National Historic Trail
El Camino Real de los Tejas National Historic Trail
Ellis Island Part of Statue of Liberty National Monument
Designation: Part of Statue of Liberty National Monument

Name: Everglades National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits the passholder and passengers of a single vehicle or vessel. Good for 7 consecutive days at all park entrances.

Name: Florissant Fossil Beds National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: $10 per adult (age 16 years or older). Admission is good for 7 days. Anyone under the age of 16 years is free. Fee covers entrance to all areas of the Monument including visitor center exhibits, film, outdoor exhibit area, hiking trails, picnic areas, Hornbek Homestead,self-guided tours, and ranger programs.

Name: Fort McHenry National Monument and Historic Shrine
Fort Pulaski National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: A site fee of $10 per person is required to visit Fort Pulaski and the surrounding areas. Admission is valid for 7 consecutive days. Youth 15 and under are admitted free of charge.

Name: Fort Smith National Historic Site
Entrance Fee Desc: The Museum is the only location that charges a fee, the fee is per person

Name: Fort Sumter and Fort Moultrie National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Fort Moultrie charges a per person entrance fee for adults. Anyone 16 years old or older is considered an adult.

Name: Fort Union Trading Post National Historic Site
Fort Vancouver National Historic Site
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance fees are required to enter Fort Vancouver for visitors ages 16 and up.

Name: Frederick Law Olmsted National Historic Site
Gates Of The Arctic National Park & Preserve
Gateway Arch National Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
When park visitors 16 and up buy tram or movie tickets, $3.00 of their ticket price goes to the National Park Service (entrance fee). Therefore, if visitors have an America the Beautiful National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Pass, they do not have to pay that $3.00 fee and they effectively get a $3.00 "discount" on the tram ride to the top and the documentary movie.

If you wish to browse in the Museum and Visitor Center, there is no entrance fee.

Name: George Rogers Clark National Historical Park
George Washington Memorial Parkway
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all its passengers. Organized groups are not eligible for the vehicle permit. Also valid for entrance into the Chesapeake and Ohio Canal National Historical Park.

Name: Glacier National Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
(Winter Rate - $25.00, November 1 to April 30)
This is a entrance fee for all persons traveling in a single, private, non-commercial vehicle (car/truck/van). The pass is good for seven days and is non-transferable. Visitors can enter the park at any time, if the entrance station is not staffed, a self-registration area is available for purchasing a 7-day park pass.

Name: Glen Canyon National Recreation Area
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all its passengers.

Name: Gloria Dei Church National Historic Site
Golden Spike National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
The per vehicle fee covers all occupants in a single private vehicle. The fee will allow visitors access to all resources open to the public, including auto tours, walking trails, films, exhibit areas, ranger guided programs, and other seasonal activities. 

If visitors have any of the America the Beautiful Inter-agency passes, these will cover the pass holder and anyone that is in their personal vehicle.

Name: Grand Canyon National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all its passengers, up to a 15 person passenger van. Organized non-commercial groups over 16 passengers require different charges. Commercial groups are not eligible for the vehicle permit.

Name: Grand Teton National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Park entrance fee for 7 days for a private, non-commercial vehicle.

Name: Great Sand Dunes National Park & Preserve
Entrance Fee Desc: Fees are charged only when the entrance station is open in the spring, summer, and fall seasons or when the visitor center is open in the winter season. Fees can be paid by cash, check, or credit card. Passes may also be purchased in advance online through recreation.gov .

Name: Guadalupe Mountains National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: An entrance fee of $10 per person (16 years of age and older) is required; entrance fees/passes permit 1-7 consecutive days of use in this national park. Holders of the Annual, Senior, Military, 4th grade and Access Pass can bring in 3 adults free of charge under their pass. Any pass must be displayed in a vehicle while in the national park.

Name: Haleakalā National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Haleakalā National Park charges a variety of fees, depending on how a visitor arrives at the park.

Name: Harpers Ferry National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: For a single, private vehicle. Excludes group tours and 7+ passenger vans. Entrance passes are valid for three consecutive days, beginning on date of purchase and are required in all park areas. Fees are payable at the Entrance Station near the park's visitor center, Bolivar Heights, Maryland Heights, Harpers Ferry Train Station, and River Access Parking Lot.

Name: Harriet Tubman Underground Railroad National Historical Park
Harry S Truman National Historic Site
Hawaiʻi Volcanoes National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Private Vehicle Pass - The private vehicle pass admits the passholder and up to 14 passengers of a single, private (non-commercial) vehicle.

Name: Historic Jamestowne Part of Colonial National Historical Park
Designation: Part of Colonial National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: For Those Without An Entrance Pass to Historic Jamestowne. Adult (16 and older) $30; good for 7 days entrance to Historic Jamestowne and Yorktown Battlefield.

Name: Home Of Franklin D Roosevelt National Historic Site
Hovenweep National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Entry fee is valid for 7 days and grants entry for driver and passengers in one private vehicle. Does not cover camping costs.

Name: Hubbell Trading Post National Historic Site
Ice Age Floods National Geologic Trail
Independence National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance to Independence Hall requires a guided tour. Tickets are required.

Name: Indiana Dunes National Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
7-Day Park Entrance Fee - Motorcycle

Per motorcycle (valid for 1-7 days from date of purchase)

Name: Isle Royale National Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
$7 per person per day to enter or remain in Isle Royale National Park. Children 15 and younger are exempt.

Visiting Park Headquarters in Houghton, MI does not require a fee.

Name: James A Garfield National Historic Site
Jean Lafitte National Historical Park and Preserve
Jewel Cave National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Scenic Tour Adult (16+) Ticket - Tickets can be reserved online at Recreation.gov up to noon the day before the tour or on a first-come, first-served basis at the park on the day of the tour. Availability of walk-up tickets is not guaranteed.

Name: John Day Fossil Beds National Monument
John Fitzgerald Kennedy National Historic Site
Joshua Tree National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: 7-day vehicle permit, admitting the passengers of a single, non-commercial vehicle on the day of purchase and for the next six days.

Name: Juan Bautista de Anza National Historic Trail
Katahdin Woods and Waters National Monument
Kennesaw Mountain National Battlefield Park
Entrance Fee Desc: The Daily Pass is valid for the date of purchase only. It admits all persons traveling in a single, private, non-commercial vehicle (car/truck/van) and is non-transferable. This pass does NOT guarantee a parking spot.

Name: Klondike Gold Rush - Seattle Unit National Historical Park
Klondike Gold Rush National Historical Park
Knife River Indian Villages National Historic Site
LBJ Memorial Grove on the Potomac
Lake Mead National Recreation Area
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits a private non-commercial vehicle for 1-7 days.

Name: Lassen Volcanic National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Valid for up to 7 consecutive days from the day of purchase at Lassen Volcanic National Park. Payable in-person at park entrances. Self-registration when not staffed.

Name: Lava Beds National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Park Entrance is $25 per vehicle and is good for 7 days.

Name: Lewis and Clark National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance fees are collected at the Fort Clatsop Visitor Center.

Name: Little Rock Central High School National Historic Site

Lyndon B Johnson National Historical Park

Marsh - Billings - Rockefeller National Historical Park
Martin Luther King, Jr. National Historical Park
Martin Van Buren National Historic Site
Mary McLeod Bethune Council House National Historic Site
Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc:
There are no fees associated with Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument.

Mississippi Civil Rights Museum does charge an admission fee to view exhibits.

Name: Mesa Verde National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This pass if good for 7 days.

Name: Montezuma Castle National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This entrance fee covers one adult, aged 16 and over, for entrance to Montezuma Castle and Tuzigoot National Monuments for 7 days.

Name: Mount Rainier National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Grants unlimited entry for one vehicle and passengers for seven consecutive days. Vehicle must be private, noncommercial, and with a seating capacity of 15 or less.

Name: National Parks of New York Harbor
Natural Bridges National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Entry fee admits one private, non-commercial vehicle driver and passengers. Entry fee is valid for 7 days.

Name: New Bedford Whaling National Historical Park
New Orleans Jazz National Historical Park
New River Gorge National Park & Preserve
Olympic National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Valid for seven consecutive days. Applies to private, non-commercial vehicles (15 passenger capacity or less). The pass covers all vehicle occupants.

Name: Organ Pipe Cactus National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee includes all occupants of a non-commercial vehicle.

Name: Oxon Cove Park & Oxon Hill Farm
Padre Island National Seashore
Entrance Fee Desc: Pass is valid for the day of purchase and the next six days for a vehicle carrying the same group of passengers. The entry fees of commercial tours are based upon the total capacity of vehicles that can carry seven or more passengers regardless of the actual number of passengers.

Name: Palo Alto Battlefield National Historical Park
Paterson Great Falls National Historical Park
Perry's Victory & International Peace Memorial
Entrance Fee Desc: Timed tickets for the Observation Desk can be purchased on the day of your visit in the Visitor Center. 16 and older are $10. Children 15 and younger are free.

Name: Petrified Forest National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one private, non-commercial vehicle (15-passenger capacity or less) and all occupants. Valid for 7 days.

Name: Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee admits the driver and all passengers in a private-use vehicle for seven consecutive days to all areas of Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore. This fee does not cover additional fees associated with camping, lighthouse tours, or commercial tours.

Name: Pipe Spring National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: There is a $10 fee per person 16 years of age and older.  Children under 15 enter for free.  This fee includes a $3/person Tribal use fee to the Kaibab Band of Paiute Indians.  All Interagency Passes are accepted.

Name: Port Chicago Naval Magazine National Memorial
President William Jefferson Clinton Birthplace Home National Historic Site
Puʻuhonua o Hōnaunau National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Admits one single, private, non-commercial vehicle and all of its passengers (up to 8 persons). Organized non-profit groups (service organizations, scouts, church groups, college/school clubs) are not eligible for the vehicle permit. Good for entry into Puʻuhonua o Hōnaunau National Historical Park for seven days from the date of purchase.

Name: Rio Grande Wild & Scenic River
Entrance Fee Desc:
Entrance Fee to Big Bend National Park.
This fee includes all occupants of a private, non-commercial vehicle and is valid for 7 days

Name: Rocky Mountain National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: 1-Day Vehicle Entrance Pass: this pass is valid for one private vehicle to enter RMNP for one day only. All passengers inside the vehicle are covered.

Name: Rosie the Riveter WWII Home Front National Historical Park
Saguaro National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: The vehicle entrance pass is sold in the form of a dated cash register receipt and admits one privately owned, non-commercial vehicle into Saguaro National Park. This includes passenger cars, trucks, vans, recreational vehicles, campers, or converted buses used for private, recreational purposes.

Name: Saint Croix Island International Historic Site
Saint Paul's Church National Historic Site
Saint-Gaudens National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Entrance fee to park grounds for people aged 16 and over. Kids aged 15 and younger are free. Valid for seven days. Fees collected 9am-4pm.

Name: Salt River Bay National Historical Park and Ecological Preserve
Designation: National Historical Park and Ecological Preserve

Name: San Antonio Missions National Historical Park
San Francisco Maritime National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc:
Credit/Debit cards preferred for payment.

Entrance to the ships is free for supervised children 15 years of age and younger.

$15 Individual Entry Pass - valid 1 through 7 days
Per person fee for visitors to the historic ships. Non-transferable. Valid for San Francisco Maritime National Historical Park.

Name: San Juan Island National Historical Park
Sand Creek Massacre National Historic Site
Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area
Saugus Iron Works National Historic Site
Selma To Montgomery National Historic Trail
Sequoia & Kings Canyon National Parks
Entrance Fee Desc: This pass is valid for 1-7 days and includes everyone traveling in a single vehicle for Sequoia & Kings Canyon National Parks and Hume Lake District of Sequoia National Forest/Giant Sequoia National Monument.

Name: Shenandoah National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Unlimited entry for one vehicle and all passengers for seven consecutive days, beginning on the day of purchase. Vehicles must be private, noncommercial, and with a seating capacity of 15 or less.

Name: Sleeping Bear Dunes National Lakeshore
Entrance Fee Desc:
Park Entrance Pass - $25.00

Per private vehicle (valid for 1-7 days from date of purchase)

Name: Sunset Crater Volcano National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This pass covers the pass holder and up to 15 passengers of a single, private (non-commercial) vehicle at both Sunset Crater Volcano and Wupatki National Monuments for 1-7 days.

Name: The White House and President's Park
Theodore Roosevelt Birthplace National Historic Site
Theodore Roosevelt Inaugural National Historic Site
Theodore Roosevelt National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Valid for 7 days for all persons traveling in a single, private, non-commercial vehicle.

Name: Thomas Edison National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Tickets for the Glenmont Estate tour can be purchased only on the Recreation.gov website.  When booking your reservation, please remember all adults and children need a ticket.  There is a $ 1.00 per ticket nonrefundable reservation fee.

Name: Timpanogos Cave National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc:
Open seasonally depending on weather.
Ages 12 and older $12.00
Ages 2 to 11 $7.00
Ages newborn to 1 $2.00
Senior/Access Pass 50% off
Timpanogos Cave National Monument can no longer accept cash or checks.

Name: Tonto National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: Tonto National Monument charges a fee to all visitors hiking to the Lower or Upper Cliff Dwelling. Tour reservations are required to visit the Upper Cliff Dwelling. The Lower Cliff Dwelling is open September through May 8:00 am to 4:00 pm and June through August 8:00 am to noon.

Name: Trail Of Tears National Historic Trail
Tule Springs Fossil Beds National Monument
Tumacácori National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: The park entrance fee is $10.00 per adult (age 16 or older) and is good for 7 days. The entrance pass is valid for seven days.

Name: Tuzigoot National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc:
Tuzigoot Entrance Fee - Per Adult - $10.00

This entrance fee covers one adult, aged 16 and over, for entrance to Montezuma Castle and Tuzigoot National Monuments for 7 days.

Name: Ulysses S Grant National Historic Site
Vicksburg National Military Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This pass admits the driver and all passengers in a private, non-commercial vehicle to the park.

Name: Virgin Islands Coral Reef National Monument
Virgin Islands National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Expanded Amenity Recreation Fee for individuals ages 16 and up.

Name: Walnut Canyon National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This pass covers the pass holder and up to 15 passengers of a single, private (non-commercial) vehicle at Walnut Canyon National Monuments for 1-7 days.

Name: War In The Pacific National Historical Park
Washington Monument
Entrance Fee Desc:
30 Day Advance Reservations - Order tickets online up to a month in advance of your visit. Inventory for the next available day (30 days out) becomes available at 10 a.m. each morning 
24-Hour Advance Reservations - Didn't get tickets in advance or planning a last minute visit? A limited number of additional tickets are made available at 10 a.m. each day for the next day's visits 
Groups may reserve up to 55 tickets up to 30 days in advance at recreation.gov ONLY. No walk ups are available for group tours.

Name: Washington-Rochambeau Revolutionary Route National Historic Trail
White Sands National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Per vehicle fee is charged to visitors for entry by a single, private non-commercial vehicle. Entrance fees are valid for reentry for seven consecutive days from the date of purchase.

Name: William Howard Taft National Historic Site
Wind Cave National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Garden of Eden Cave Tour Adult Ticket - These can be purchased 3-120 days in advance on Recreation.gov or at the park on a first-come, first-served basis on the day of the tour.

Name: Wolf Trap National Park for the Performing Arts
Wrangell - St Elias National Park & Preserve
Wright Brothers National Memorial
Entrance Fee Desc: Fee is charged per-person, NOT per vehicle. Ages 15 and younger are free of charge.

Name: Wupatki National Monument
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee covers the occupants of one private vehicle for seven days at both Sunset Crater Volcano and Wupatki National Monuments.

Name: Yellowstone National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Unlimited entry for one vehicle and all passengers for seven consecutive days, beginning on the day of purchase. Vehicles must be private, non-commercial, and with a seating capacity of 15 or less.

Name: Yorktown Battlefield Part of Colonial National Historical Park
Designation: Part of Colonial National Historical Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Adult (16 and older) -$15; good for 7 days entrance to Yorktown Battlefield (and NPS areas at Historic Jamestowne); can be upgraded to see Preservation Virginia areas at Historic Jamestowne for an additional $15 at the Historic Jamestowne Visitor Center. Yorktown Battlefield will not be selling the $30 entrance permit for Historic Jamestowne

Name: Yosemite National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: This fee is valid for seven consecutive days for a non-commercial car, pickup truck, RV, or van with 15 or fewer passenger seats.

Name: Zion National Park
Entrance Fee Desc: Rangers may ask to see permits at the Grotto or Scout Lookout. Hikers may see a ranger on the trail at any time of day or night. If you have a permit, do not forget to print or download your permit confirmation email before you start the hike. You may need to show this and identification to a ranger on the trail.
